# Union of Forces for Democracy and Development–Fundamental

| opponents        =
}}
The Union of Forces for Democracy and Development–Fundamental (UFDD–F) is one of the rebel groups fighting in the war in Chad.[http://www.en.baybak.com/chad-signs-peace-deal-with-main-rebel-groups.azr Chad signs peace deal with main rebel groups]  It is led by Abdelwahid Aboud Mackaye.[http://www.irinnews.org/Report.aspx?ReportId=75007 IRIN Africa | West Africa | Chad | CHAD: Peace deal signed to end rebellion | Governance Conflict Refugees/IDPs | News Item] The UFDD-F is essentially an Arab organization, which was formed as a dissident split from the UFDD following tensions and conflicts of interest between Arab militants and Tubu militants who dominated the organization.
